# Paideia — Always-On Rules

You are building **Paideia**: a content-less LMS where an AI agent generates a
course one lesson at a time, adapting to each student. Full context: `AGENTS.md`.

## Before any task
1. Read `AGENTS.md` if you have not this session.
2. Read the specific `tasks/phase-0N.md` you're working on.
3. For any requirement code (e.g. `SESS-04`, `AGENT-09`, `AC-03`), look it up in
   `docs/fsd.md`. For API shapes, data model, or architecture, use `docs/tsd.md`.
   For anything visual, use `docs/design-system.md`.

## Non-negotiable stack facts
- **Auth = Django + simplejwt. NOT Clerk.** The User model is the identity. Bearer JWT.
- **Streaming = `fetch()` + ReadableStream. NEVER EventSource** (POST endpoint).
- **DB driver = `psycopg` v3** (`psycopg[binary]`), async ORM inside the async view.
- **Anthropic via `AsyncAnthropic`**, model from `ANTHROPIC_MODEL_VERSION` env var.
- **Interactive blocks** = sandboxed iframe `srcDoc`, `sandbox="allow-scripts"`,
  no `allow-same-origin`; CSP via injected `<meta>`; failure via `postMessage`
  `paideia:ready` handshake + 4s timeout. Never `onError`, never the iframe `csp` attr.
- **No FAILED session state** — failed generation deletes the row.
- **Cross-scope reads return 404**, not 403.

## Design tokens (canonical)
Fraunces (display) · Geist (body) · JetBrains Mono (meta). Canvas `#FAF6EE`
(parchment, never pure white). Primary ink-blue `#1C2A4A`. Accent ochre `#B8862C`.
Buttons 6px, cards 10px. Earth-palette subjects, no bright primaries.

## Code conventions
- API shape change ⇒ Django serializer + `frontend/lib/schemas.ts` zod schema in the SAME commit.
- `backend/agent/` stays pure: no imports from accounts/courses/sessions, no Django, no DB.
- Every test gets an ID: `T-W{n}-{nn}` (unit), `T-SEAM-W{n}` (seam).
- A wave is done only when its exit criteria pass. Don't start the next wave early.

## When unsure
Prefer asking or leaving a `// TODO(spec): <question>` over inventing behaviour
that isn't in the specs. Hallucinated requirements are worse than flagged gaps.
